Eskom has not received payment from Zimbabwe 28 June 2019 Eskom would like to state that no funds have reflected on its accounts for Zimbabwe’s outstanding debt as at 28 June at 15h00. This is in response to the announcement made in Zimbabwe and queries that Eskom is receiving regarding this issue. “Once Eskom has received the funds, we will then enter into further discussions with Zesa,” Eskom Group Chief Executive Phakamani Hadebe said. Issued by Eskom Media Desk, 29 June 2019